io        =\n| genre         = \n| length        = {{Duration|m=4|s=00}}\n| label         = {{hlist|Erskine|[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]}}\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[Harry Styles]]|[[Kid Harpoon|Thomas Hull]]}}\n| producer      = {{hlist|[[Kid Harpoon]]}}\n| prev_title    = [[Adore You (Harry Styles song)|Adore You]]\n| prev_year     = 2019\n| next_title    =\n| next_year     =\n| misc          = \n}}\n\n\"'''Falling'''\" is a song by English singer and songwriter [[Harry Styles]]. It was released through Erskine and [[Columbia Records]] on 7 March 2020 as the fourth single from his second studio album, ''[[Fine Line (album)|Fine Line]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7907021/harry-styles-readies-a-video-for-new-fine-line-single-falling|title=Harry Styles Readies A Video For New &#8216;Fine Line&#8217; Single &#8220;Falling&#8221;|date=2020-02-24|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video, directed by [[Dave Meyers (director)|Dave Meyers]], was released on 28 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8551716/harry-styles-falling-video-teaser|title=Harry Styles Announces 'Falling' Video With Water-Soaked Teaser: Watch|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nerdsandbeyond.com/2020/02/24/harry-styles-will-release-falling-music-video-on-february-28/|title=Harry Styles Will Release \"Falling\" Music Video On February 28|date=2020-02-24|website=Nerds and Beyond|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> The video features Styles alone in an apartment with a piano. As he sings the ballad, the room slowly fills with water, until, in the end, he is fully submerged, drowning. In reference to the video, Styles said \"That feeling of kind of being overwhelmed, you know you can feel like you're drowning sometimes...and the fact that it's coming from the piano, I guess it's like writing these songs are what helps but also they can hurt you sometimes.\"\n\n==Live performances==\nOn 18 February 2020, Styles performed the song for the first time on [[2020 Brit Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-falling-brit-awards-954729/|title=Watch Harry Styles Perform 'Falling' at 2020 BRIT Awards|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=2020-02-19|website=Rolling Stone|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/harry-styles-performs-at-brit-awards-watch-video.html|title=Harry Styles Floods the Stage During Emotional Performance at the BRIT Awards|last=Alter|first=Rebecca|date=2020-02-18|website=Vulture|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nThe song debuted at number 39 in the UK, giving Styles his fifth top 40 entry there. It later reached number 20 in March 2020 for 3 weeks,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51376/harry-styles/|title=Official Charts, Harry Styles|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> making it the third top 20 single and fourth top 20 song from ''Fine Line'' and Styles' fifth solo top 20 overall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2020/03/24/harry-styles-the-killers-niall-horan-and-drake-5-major-moves-on-this-weeks-uk-singles-chart/#2d4c85e17c70|title=Harry Styles, The Killers, Niall Horan And Drake: 5 Major Moves On This Week's U.K. Singles Chart|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|date=2020-03-24|website=Forbes|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> It peaked at number 16 in April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20200416/7501|title=Official Charts, Harry Styles, Single:Falling, Week of April 16|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> The song certified Silver on April 2020, making it the album's 4th single to achieve Silver or higher. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BRITs/status/1246078500693364736|title=@Harry_Styles's single 'Falling', the 3rd song from his latest album to reach the UK Top 20, has gone #BRITcertified Silver!|publisher=BRIT Awards, Twitter|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpi.co.uk/award/13567-4394-1|title=British single certifications \u2013 Harry Styles \u2013 Falling. British Phonographic Industry|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\nThe song is certified Gold in the US, making it Styles's sixth single to be certified Gold or higher.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&ar=HARRY+STYLES|title=GOLD & PLATINUM, RIAA, Harry Styles|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|35|artist=Harry Styles|song=Falling|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|55|artist=Harry Styles|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Croatia ([[Croatian Radiotelevision|HRT]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://radio.hrt.hr/clanak/arc-100-datum-6-travnja-2020/226648/|title=Croatia ARC TOP 100|publisher=HRT|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 53\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|69|year=2019|week=51|rowheader=true|accessdate=5 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|title=Official IFPI Charts \u2013 Digital Singles Chart (International) \u2013 Week: 51/2019|publisher=[[IFPI Greece]]|accessdate=15 April 2020|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230175929/http://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|archivedate=30 December 2019}}</ref>\n| 51\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland3|22|artist=Harry Styles|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-w51/|title=2019 51-os SAVAIT\u0116S (gruod\u017eio 13-19 d.) (TOP 100)|language=Lithuanian|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|date=20 December 2019|accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 33\n|-\n{{single chart|New Zealand|24|artist=Harry Styles|song=Falling|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Portugal|43|artist=Harry Styles|song=Falling|rowheader=true|accessdate=5 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|6|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=11 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Slovakdigital|74|year=2020|week=02|rowheader=true|accessdate=5 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| South Korea ([[Gaon Digital Chart|Gaon]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=10&hitYear=2020&termGbn=week|title=Digital Chart \u2013 Week 10 of 2020|website=Gaon Chart|language=ko|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 157\n|-\n{{single chart|Sweden|81|artist=Harry Styles|song=Falling|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|16|date=20200410|rowheader=true|accessdate=11 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|62|artist=Harry Styles|rowheader=true|accessdate=29 February 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/songs/2019-12-13/|title=Top 100 Songs|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 34\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|award=Silver|id=13567-4394-1|artist=Harry Styles|title=Falling|date=3 April 2020|relyear=2019|certyear=2020|accessdate=10 April 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|award=Gold||artist=Harry Styles|title=Falling|date=27 March 2020|relyear=2019|certyear=2020|accessdate=30 March 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!Region\n!Date\n!Format\n!Label\n!{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row| Various\n|13 December 2019\n|{{hlist|[[Music download|Digital downloa